DURBAN - It won’t be a Merry Christmas for the residents of Foreman Road Informal Settlement in Durban. More than 500 were left homeless when their shacks caught fire a month ago. Three family members, one a three-year-old boy, died in the fire. READ: Blaze destroys Durban informal settlement The festive season has been bleak, difficult and not worth celebrating for many of the people living in Foreman Road Informal Settlement. According to the residents, of the 500 people who were affected by the fire, only 50 have been provided with materials to rebuild their homes. The eThekwini Municipality, however, says there are plans in place to develop the area. eNCA